<h3>CULTURE</h3>
	<h3><a href = "http://www.flickr.com/search/?q=Kapaleeswarar+Temple" target="_newtab">Kapaleeswarar Temple</a></h3>
	<p>A 7<sup>th</sup> Century CE Hindu temple built during the Pallava rule. It holds immense mythological significance and is a marquee landmark in Mylapore.</p>
	<a href ="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kapaleeswarar_Temple" target="_newtab">Wikipedia</a><br>
	<a href ="http://goo.gl/maps/dvZEV" target="_newtab">Directions</a><br>
		
	<h3><a href = "http://www.flickr.com/search/?q=Santhome+Church" target="_newtab">San Thome Basilica</a></h3>
	<p>A 16<sup>th</sup> Century  Roman Catholic (Latin Rite) minor basilica in Santhome. It was built by Portuguese explorers, over the tomb of St. Thomas, an apostle of Jesus.</p>
	<a href ="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Santhome_Church" target="_newtab">Wikipedia</a><br>
	<a href ="http://goo.gl/maps/Gyhh7" target="_newtab">Directions</a><br>
	
	<h3><a href = "http://www.flickr.com/search/?q=Kalakshetra" target="_newtab">Kalakshetra</a></h3>
	<p>A cultural academy dedicated to the preservation of traditional values in Indian art, especially in the field of Bharatanatyam dance and Gandharvaveda music.</p>
	<a href ="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kalakshetra" target="_newtab">Wikipedia</a><br>
	<a href ="http://goo.gl/maps/0IXmG" target="_newtab">Directions</a><br>
	
	<h3><a href = "http://www.flickr.com/search/?q=Dakshinchitra" target="_newtab">Dakshin Chitra</a></h3>
